Definition.WordDefinition: liftoff \liftoff\ n. (Rocketry) the initial ascent of a rocket from its launching pad. [WordNet 1.5]
lift off v : depart from the ground; "The plane took off two hours late" [syn: {take off}]
liftoff n : the initial ascent of a rocket from its launching pad
